 The ties are historical and political. However, government's decision to give the Republic of Cuba R50-million in aid has come under scrutiny. Slindelo Masikane reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Government is arguing that AfriForum’s court bid against a R50-million donation to Cuba is premature. Various civil society organisations and South Africans have expressed outrage at the planned aid, given the socio-economic need locally. Cuba is said to be facing chronic shortages of food, fuel, medicine and electricity. WATCH: SA's special intervention | SA's R50m donation to Cuba According to lawyers, the international relations department is well within its right to donate the money through its African Renaissance and International Cooperation Fund. Judgment has been reserved. * eNCA's Slindelo Masikane reports.